Tracy,
=20
Here are the answers:
=20
(1).  Software installations are done by primarily by Software, but =
Service can reinstall software, and Hardware installs images on new =
systems based on Software Section recommendations.  Networking installs =
server software on their servers.  Yes, it can depend on the software.
=20
(2).  It depends on the operation environment NetWare, NT, Unix.  Each has =
their own way of performing automated software installs.  Microsoft =
handles this using global and local policies with Windows 2000 Active =
Directory Server.  Novell (NetWare) has similar capabilities using =
Zenworks.  I and not sure how Unix servers would/could do this.  There are =
different identifiers that could be used.  Login name, workstation id, MAC =
address, it all depends on the operating system.
We have done any specific cost analysis.  If you stop and consider how =
long it could take one technical to reinstall software for one user =
manually as opposed to some automated method the cost is substantial.
Yes, it is possible to perform an automatic (non-manual) install from the =
network to a specific room.
=20
If a more technical response is needed please let me know.
=20
Tony=20
=20
